      <para id="id207839">We have a related m-function <emphasis effect="italics">idbn</emphasis> for obtaining the joint probability matrix
from the marginal probabilities. Its formation of the joint matrix utilizes
the same operations as icalc.</para>


<example id="fs-id1167701331714"><title>A numerical example</title><code id="id207859" display="block">PX = 0.1*[3 5 2];
PY = 0.01*[20 15 40 25];
P  = idbn(PX,PY)
P =
    0.0750    0.1250    0.0500
